(65, 1, '2015-01-14 01:20:43', '2015-01-14 01:20:43', 'Session Kitchen was inspired by the ‘sessions’ and the ‘flow and motion’ found in the cultures of action sports, music and street art. The Ceiling Element was designed as both a light fixture and a mood generator with videos, shapes and colors projecting across the 40 foot long bar. The colors, speed and projection can all be controlled by a custom tablet app giving the ability to manage the piece based on the time of day and vibe of the crowd.\r\n\r\nJen Lewin    |    <a title="bldgcollective" href="http://www.bldgcollective.com/" target="_blank">Bldg.Collective</a>    |    <a title="Lumigeek" href="http://lumigeek.com/" target="_blank">Lumigeek</a>', 'The Ceiling Element', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-ceiling-element', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:22:01', '2015-02-28 18:22:01', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=art&#038;p=65', 0, 'art', '', 0),
(70, 1, '2015-01-15 01:21:24', '2015-01-15 01:21:24', 'The Butterfly is a 10′ tall handmade interactive silk creature that moves and lights in response to human closeness. Approaching The Butterfly ‘wakes it up’ and causes it to react to you with movement - Each wing has 6 different areas that can sense human movement. As you move closer to a wing, it will move away from you at the same speed of your movement. Through curious interactions you can dance and play with a larger than life silk butterfly.\r\n\r\nEach butterfly wing is a synthesis of silk, paint, and electronics. The butterfly wings are controlled by specially designed and printed circuit boards and analog proximity circuits cut to fit within the painted silk. Woven LEDS run from these boards throughout the painted wings, lighting up in animation as a user is near.\r\n\r\nThe butterfly eye piece is composed of 2 lenses, a small TV screen and hidden video camera that captures and projects the user. From afar, the piece glows with abstract pixels that resemble the curvature of an actual insect eye. Only when up close (very close) do you begin to see actual shapes in the lens….. on closer inspection these shapes become eyes, and even closer, you realize the eyes are your own.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'The Butterfly', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-butterfly', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:21:51', '2015-02-28 18:21:51', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=art&#038;p=70', 0, 'art', '', 0),
(72, 1, '2015-01-16 01:21:36', '2015-01-16 01:21:36', 'The Light Curtain is a private commissioned to create an illuminated threshold.  The Light Curtain is created from hand woven fibers and LEDS the reflects light and movement from its environment.', 'The Light Curtain', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-light-curtain', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:21:41', '2015-02-28 18:21:41', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=art&#038;p=72', 0, 'art', '', 0),
(74, 1, '2015-01-17 01:21:49', '2015-01-17 01:21:49', 'The Moths are three soft interactive robotic forms that are charged to movement by human connection. The Moths are a participatory art piece; only by stopping and connecting physically do they come to life. The longer one stays, the longer the moth will continue to move even when the viewer leaves. The Moths speak to light, to community, to gathering, and have an open ethereal dream like quality that will gracefully dance and glow in space.', 'The Moths', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-moths', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:21:30', '2015-02-28 18:21:30', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=art&#038;p=74', 0, 'art', '', 0),
(76, 1, '2015-01-18 01:22:03', '2015-01-18 01:22:03', 'The Paint Torch is a permanent outdoor sculpture by Claes Oldenburg.\r\n\r\nIn 2010, Oldenburg and I met to discuss ways to elegantly incorporate technology and illumination within his proposed piece The Paint Torch.  He had been inspired by some of my art work in particular several FRP illuminated pieces I created with <a title="Kreysler and Associates" href="http://kreysler.com/" target="_blank">Kreysler and Associates</a> in California.   We began working together almost immediately, spending over 12 months developing the sublet, yet elegant internal ‘glow’ you now see within the piece.\r\n\r\n<a title="Claes Oldenburg" href="http://oldenburgvanbruggen.com/" target="_blank">Claes Oldenburg</a>    |    Jen Lewin', 'The Paint Torch', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-paint-torch', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:21:18', '2015-02-28 18:21:18', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=art&#038;p=76', 0, 'art', '', 0),
(80, 1, '2015-01-19 01:22:54', '2015-01-19 01:22:54', 'The Pointers are three large illuminated arrows mounted on articulating arms against a wall.\r\n\r\nParticipants are invited to point and rotate the arrows as desired, allowing the audience to impact the art changes the perceived impact. They appear to display different messages and emotional reactions when all three are pointed down, or up, or at the gallery attendant to the left. The artistic intention, however, remains the same - that by impacting the art you have more of a connection to your community than just being a passive observer.', 'The Pointers', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-pointers', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:21:01', '2015-02-28 18:21:01', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=art&#038;p=80', 0, 'art', '', 0),
(82, 1, '2015-01-21 01:23:04', '2015-01-21 01:23:04', '<a title="The Kitchen Community" href="https://thekitchencommunity.org/" target="_blank">The Kitchen Community</a>\r\n\r\nA Learning Garden is a permanent, organic garden that includes fruit trees, shrubs and raised vegetable beds that provide an interactive outdoor space to connect children with real food. The Kitchen’s Learning Garden was specially designed by Jen Lewin Studios as an educational tool to inspire spontaneous play by children and create an attractive outdoor classroom for teachers. Unlike simple garden beds, a Learning Garden comprises modular beds with built-in irrigation systems that can be shaped in any configuration to fit small and large plots in virtually every schoolyard. Its feminine and organic lines contrasts with the concrete and harsh lines of cities and inspires a natural reaction from students and teachers alike. The Learning Garden design also includes hand-painted signs by children to increase their ownership of the garden.\r\n\r\nThe Kitchen Community has helped nearly 200 schools in Colorado, California, Illinois and Tennessee.', 'The Learning Garden', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-learning-garden', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:17:49', '2015-02-28 18:17:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=art&#038;p=82', 0, 'art', '', 0),
(86, 1, '2015-01-22 01:23:35', '2015-01-22 01:23:35', 'The Water Tree is a sculpture by Denver based artist Lawrence Argent.\r\n\r\nLawrence Argent approached me in the fall of 2009 after seeing my interactive light sculpture <a href="http://jenlewinstudio.com/community-sculpture/the-pool/">The Pool</a>.  He asked if I could create, design and install a similar LED lighting system in his sculpture, The Water Tree. The Water tree is composed of 52 fiberglass, wireless, organic, LED forms.\r\n\r\n<a title="Lawrence Argent" href="http://www.lawrenceargent.com/" target="_blank">Lawrence Argent</a>    |    Jen Lewin', 'The Water Tree', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-water-tree', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:17:27', '2015-02-28 18:17:27', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=art&#038;p=86', 0, 'art', '', 0),
(90, 1, '2015-01-01 01:24:27', '2015-01-01 01:24:27', 'The Edison Orb  is homage to the incandescent light bulb, which stopped US production and import  in  2012.\r\n\r\nThe Edison Orb is created from formed aluminum rings and customized, clear custom made incandescent bulbs. Derived in form from the original designs and molds from The Pool, it is a beautiful example of recycling beauty and function. The fixtures, handmade in Boulder, Colorado, cast a unique light pattern and transform spaces from private homes to commercial spaces. Featured in <a href="http://thekitchen.com/">The Kitchen</a> restaurants nationwide.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'The Edison Orb', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'the-edison-orb', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:30:38', '2015-02-28 18:30:38', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=objects&#038;p=90', 0, 'objects', '', 0),
(92, 1, '2015-01-02 01:24:44', '2015-01-02 01:24:44', 'The Edison Orb  is homage to the incandescent light bulb, which stopped US production and import  in  2012. The fixtures, handmade in Boulder, Colorado, cast a unique light pattern and transform spaces from private homes to commercial spaces. Featured in <a href="http://thekitchen.com/">The Kitchen</a> restaurants nationwide.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'The Edison Chandelier', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'the-edison-chandelier', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:30:34', '2015-02-28 18:30:34', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=objects&#038;p=92', 0, 'objects', '', 0),
(94, 1, '2015-01-04 01:25:25', '2015-01-04 01:25:25', 'The Arc Lamps are five individual chandeliers constructed out of recycled oversized light bulbs and custom LED lights. Constructed in 2013 and debuted at the <a title="Biennial of the Americas" href="http://www.biennialoftheamericas.org/">Biennale of the Americas</a> in Denver, they make an impact both near and far. The design was based off of The Edison Chandelier, using a similar construction but pushing the boundaries of scale by incorporating bulbs still being used in commercial lighting. The Arc Lamps currently hang in <a title="The Studio (Boulder)" href="http://thestudioboulder.com" target="_blank">The Studio (Boulder)</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'The Arc Lamps', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'the-arc-lamps', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:27:16', '2015-02-28 18:27:16', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=objects&#038;p=94', 0, 'objects', '', 0),
(98, 1, '2015-01-05 01:25:57', '2015-01-05 01:25:57', 'Created from custom hand cut thick Pyrex, The Kitchen Sconce and The Kitchen Pendant were designed and are featured in <a title="The Kitchen" href="http://thekitchen.com/" target="_blank">The Kitchen</a> restaurants nationwide. Mixing clean simple aesthetic with vintage forms, these fixtures blends function and beauty.\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>', 'The Kitchen Pendant and Sconce', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'the-kitchen-pendent', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:26:47', '2015-02-28 18:26:47', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=objects&#038;p=98', 0, 'objects', '', 0),
(100, 1, '2015-01-02 01:26:13', '2015-01-02 01:26:13', 'Architecture &amp; Interior Design, Branding, Graphic Design and Product Design\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBoulder    |    Denver    |    Fort Collins    |    Chicago\r\n\r\nFounders Jen Lewin    |    Hugo Matheson    |    Kimbal Musk', 'The Kitchen', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'the-kitchen', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:33:11', '2015-02-28 18:33:11', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=spaces&#038;p=100', 0, 'spaces', '', 0),
