(595, 1, '2015-01-26 22:49:05', '2015-01-26 22:49:05', 'The Arc Lamps are five individual chandeliers constructed out of recycled oversized light bulbs and custom LED lights. Constructed in 2013 and debuted at the <a title="Biennial of the Americas" href="http://www.biennialoftheamericas.org/">Biennale of the Americas</a> in Denver, they make an impact both near and far. The design was based off of The Edison Chandelier, using a similar construction but pushing the boundaries of scale by incorporating bulbs still being used in commercial lighting. The Arc Lamps currently hang in <a title="The Studio (Boulder)" href="http://thestudioboulder.com" target="_blank">The Studio (Boulder)</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>Some Photography by <a title="Davis Tilly Photography" href="http://www.davistilly.com/" target="_blank">Ashley Davis / Davis Tilly Photography</a>', 'The Arc Lamps', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '94-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-26 22:49:05', '2015-01-26 22:49:05', '', 94, 'http://jenlewinstudio.com/94-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(596, 1, '2015-01-26 22:54:24', '2015-01-26 22:54:24', 'The Edison Orb  is homage to the incandescent light bulb, which stopped US production and import  in  2012. The fixtures, handmade in Boulder, Colorado, cast a unique light pattern and transform spaces from private homes to commercial spaces. Featured in <a href="http://thekitchen.com/">The Kitchen</a> restaurants nationwide.\r\n\r\nEmail <a href="mailto:info@jenlewinstudio.com">info@jenlewinstudio.com</a> for more information.', 'The Edison Chandelier', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '92-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-26 22:54:24', '2015-01-26 22:54:24', '', 92, 'http://jenlewinstudio.com/92-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
