(667, 1, '2015-02-03 20:31:24', '2015-02-03 20:31:24', 'The Last Ocean is an interactive light environment designed by Jen Lewin. It is composed of a sea of interactive, wireless, waterproof light platforms that span over a quarter of a mile. By entering The Ocean, you enter a world where play and collaborative movement create a cascading effect of swirling light and color.\r\n<h4>INTERACTION:</h4>\r\nAt night The Ocean will glow blue. Each of The Ocean’s ice platforms will sense user movement and position. By walking over and through the ice, you will create swirls of white and blue light in your wake.\r\n\r\nDuring the day, The Ocean will reflect the existing sky. Each ice platform is created from highly resilient fiberglass, embedded LEDS and a durable reflective (mirror coating.) Viewers will experience the sensation of walking over a sea of blue glass.', 'The Last Ocean', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-last-ocean', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:14:43', '2015-02-28 18:14:43', '', 0, 'http://jenlewinstudio.com/?post_type=art&#038;p=667', 0, 'art', '', 0),
(668, 1, '2015-02-03 20:31:24', '2015-02-03 20:31:24', 'The Last Ocean is an interactive light environment designed by Jen Lewin. It is composed of a sea of interactive, wireless, waterproof light platforms that span over a quarter of a mile. By entering The Ocean, you enter a world where play and collaborative movement create a cascading effect of swirling light and color.\r\n<h4>INTERACTION:</h4>\r\nAt night The Ocean will glow blue. Each of The Ocean’s ice platforms will sense user movement and position. By walking over and through the ice, you will create swirls of white and blue light in your wake.\r\n\r\nDuring the day, The Ocean will reflect the existing sky. Each ice platform is created from highly resilient fiberglass, embedded LEDS and a durable reflective (mirror coating.) Viewers will experience the sensation of walking over a sea of blue glass.', 'The Last Ocean', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '667-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-03 20:31:24', '2015-02-03 20:31:24', '', 667, 'http://jenlewinstudio.com/667-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(669, 1, '2015-02-03 20:38:21', '2015-02-03 20:38:21', '<div class="page" title="Page 2">\r\n<div class="layoutArea">\r\n<div class="column">\r\n\r\nAqueous is a new piece based on my work The Pool. Like The Pool, it will engage large groups of participants in active, community play. Aqueous will transform public space using form and light to create a beautiful and participatory connected user experience.\r\n\r\nThe Pool started with a basic idea: Can you engage over 100 people (all ages and all cultures), with light and play in a dynamic community sculpture? It has since been all over the world to over 40 major exhibits, some with over 10,000 participants per hour. The Pool is designed to install in only a few hours, and break down in less. It is durable, water proof, and ready to travel!\r\n\r\nAqueous is a progression of this idea – while The Pool drew people together, Aqueous will move people in shared direction. Some people will run, some will skip, others might sit, crawl or roll, but what’s important is that they will be together on the same path for event the briefest of moments.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Aqueous', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'aqueous', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:13:52', '2015-02-28 18:13:52', '', 0, 'http://jenlewinstudio.com/?post_type=art&#038;p=669', 0, 'art', '', 0),
