(930, 1, '2015-02-11 23:32:15', '2015-02-11 23:32:15', 'The Pointers are three large illuminated arrows mounted on articulating arms against a wall.\r\n\r\nParticipants are invited to point and rotate the arrows as desired, allowing the audience to impact the art changes the perceived impact. They appear to display different messages and emotional reactions when all three are pointed down, or up, or at the gallery attendant to the left. The artistic intention, however, remains the same - that by impacting the art you have more of a connection to your community than just being a passive observer.', 'The Pointers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '80-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-11 23:32:15', '2015-02-11 23:32:15', '', 80, 'http://jenlewinstudio.com/80-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(931, 1, '2015-02-11 23:35:07', '2015-02-11 23:35:07', 'The Ms are a playful series of classic American logobilia transformed through public interaction. Whether it be in commerce, effort or time, it’s undeniable that there are symbols that have become an unrecognizable part of life. The Ms allow participants to interact with some of these symbols without cultural pressure and reminds us that their real meaning lies in playful moments. Mounted on articulating arms, participants can impact and change these pieces to be playful, traditional, ironic, or nonsensical.', 'The Ms', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '561-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-11 23:35:07', '2015-02-11 23:35:07', '', 561, 'http://jenlewinstudio.com/561-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(933, 1, '2015-02-11 23:39:56', '2015-02-11 23:39:56', '<a title="The Kitchen Community" href="https://thekitchencommunity.org/" target="_blank">The Kitchen Community</a>\r\n\r\nA Learning Garden is a permanent, organic garden that includes fruit trees, shrubs and raised vegetable beds that provide an interactive outdoor space to connect children with real food. The Kitchen’s Learning Garden was specially designed by Jen Lewin Studios as an educational tool to inspire spontaneous play by children and create an attractive outdoor classroom for teachers. Unlike simple garden beds, a Learning Garden comprises modular beds with built-in irrigation systems that can be shaped in any configuration to fit small and large plots in virtually every schoolyard. Its feminine and organic lines contrasts with the concrete and harsh lines of cities and inspires a natural reaction from students and teachers alike. The Learning Garden design also includes hand-painted signs by children to increase their ownership of the garden.\r\n\r\nThe Kitchen Community has helped nearly 200 schools in Colorado, California, Illinois and Tennessee.', 'The Learning Garden', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '82-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-11 23:39:56', '2015-02-11 23:39:56', '', 82, 'http://jenlewinstudio.com/82-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
