.sparkfun.com/tutorials/193" target="_blank">Sparkfun: Jen Lewin Feature</a>\r\n<h4>DESIGN</h4>\r\n<a title="The Feel Good Kitchen, Food and Wine Magazine" href="http://www.foodandwine.com/articles/the-feel-good-kitchen" target="_blank">The Feel Good Kitchen, Food and Wine Magazine</a>\r\n<p id="page-title"><a title="TedX- Reinventing the role of restaurants in changing America’s Food Culture, Kimbal Musk" href="http://tedxtalks.ted.com/video/TEDxBOULDER-Kimbal-Musk-Reinven" target="_blank">TedX- Reinventing the role of restaurants in changing America’s Food Culture, Kimbal Musk</a></p>\r\n<a title="Denver Post Feature: “Jen Lewin designs The Kitchen Denver to savor simplicity”" href="http://www.denverpost.com/ci_20445918/jen-lewin-kitchen-denver" target="_blank">Denver Post Feature: “Jen Lewin designs The Kitchen Denver to savor simplicity”</a>\r\n\r\n<a title="Green Up Colorado" href="http://video.rmpbs.org/video/1893650385/" target="_blank">Green Up Colorado</a> - A film about sustainability and green living, a film by Lisa D. Olken.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Press Contact</h4>\r\nJulie Miller<a href="mailto:julie@jenlewinstudio.com?Subject=Press%20Contact" target="_top">\r\njulie@jenlewinstudio.com</a>\r\n\r\n[/efstab]\r\n[/efstabs]', 'About Jen Lewin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '108-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:41:43', '2015-02-28 18:41:43', '', 108, 'http://jenlewinstudio.com/108-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1243, 1, '2015-02-28 18:44:07', '2015-02-28 18:44:07', '<h4 class="space-top">JAMIE WIRKLER _PRODUCT AND DESIGN DIRECTOR</h4>\r\nJamie received his B.A. in Environmental Design from the University of Colorado at Boulder. After graduating, he took on the role of Product Manager at The Kitchen Community (TKC), a Boulder-based (501c3) startup. He assisted in design of the Learning Garden – a Jen Lewin designed modular garden system – various products and established a network of inventory and distribution channels. Other work for TKC included project management, landscape design, and marketing, where Jamie worked with a talented team to launch a nationwide campaign around encouraging families to cook at home.\r\n\r\nHis curiosity for the built environment fuels his interest in how design using light, motion, sound and the outdoors impact our ability to come together as a community. Jamie is currently exploring his curiosity as the Product and Design Director at Jen Lewin Studio.\r\n\r\n<a href="mailto:jamie@jenlewinstudio.com">jamie@jenlewinstudio.com</a>\r\n<h4>WILLIAM GOODRICH_LEAD ENGINEER</h4>\r\nWilliam is a multi-disciplined engineer and creative technologist with experience in product development, electronics hardware, and a multitude of sensor technologies. After receiving a dual bachelor’s degree in Engineering and Philosophy from Lafayette College, William traversed a range of professions from teaching high school science and math to civil and energy engineering to electronics technology.  Working under accomplished engineer Gus Calabrese, he has prototyped products ranging from an inductive mobile device charger to a remote environmental sensing platform and contributed to the repair of security card swipe readers for several nuclear power plants on the east coast.  William has worked with Jen Lewin on all aspects of many of her sculptural pieces and provides engineering expertise for new projects.  William is also co-founder of The Studio (Boulder), the community workspace where Jen Lewin Studio resides.\r\n\r\n<a href="mailto:william@jenlewinstudio.com">william@jenlewinstudio.com</a>\r\n<h4>JULIE MILLER _LOGISTICAL IDEATION</h4>\r\nlo·gis·ti·cal ide·a·tion: Business Development, Media and Content Strategy, Marketing and Art\r\n\r\nJulie has several previous lives. Most recent include being a professional video editor in Denver utilizing her BFA in Film Post-Production from the Colorado Film School and owning and operating a small flooring installation company. In the much more distant past, Julie was a monk in medieval France and a house frau in turn of the century Germany.\r\n\r\nJulie’s turn offs: turtles, copyright infringement and meanies.\r\n\r\nJulie’s turn ons: digital strategy, obscure movie references and moral media.\r\n\r\n<a href="mailto:julie@jenlewinstudio.com">julie@jenlewinstudio.com</a>\r\n<h4>CHARLES LINDGREN_LOGISTICS</h4>\r\nCharlie Lindgren stepped into dual roles as fabricator and logistics officer for Jen Lewin Studio in June of 2014. He previously worked with JLS in over the summer of 2012, primarily as an escort for The Pool on its southwestern journey to Electric Daisy Carnivals in Dallas and Las Vegas. Charlie is a May 2014 graduate of the University of Colorado with a degree in International Affairs and a minor in Economics. A student of international politics and policy and an avid traveler, Charlie pursued fluency in Spanish while at CU and continues this pursuit. Other interests include reading, Star Wars, snowboarding and all things CU Athletics. Go Buffs!\r\n\r\n<a href="mailto:charlie@jenlewinstudio.com">charlie@jenlewinstudio.com</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Studio Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '113-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-28 18:44:07', '2015-02-28 18:44:07', '', 113, 'http://jenlewinstudio.com/113-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
